The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Adani boss gets bail after arrest
                                                                                                                           6                                                                                      Adani boss gets bail after arrest
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT AMP; PTI                              
	Ahmedabad, Feb. 27: The Central Bureau of Investigation (CBI) today arrested Rajesh Adani, managing director of Adani Wilmar Ltd, for allegedly evading customs duty worth over 50 crore.        
	He was later granted bail by Gujarat High Court. The court has issued a notice to CBI and granted interim bail to Adani. The next hearing is scheduled for Tuesday next week.        
	Rajesh is the younger brother of Gautam Adani, group chairman of the Rs 60,000-crore Gujarat-based Adani Enterprises.        
	A CBI team arrested Rajesh Adani from Ahmedabads Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel airport today morning. A case was registered against him in 2008. After his arrest, Adani complained of chest pain and high blood pressure and was taken to the Gandhinagar Civil Hospital for a check-up.        
	Adani Enterprises Ltd said in a statement, The company is surprised and pursuing the matter with the assistance of its legal counsel.        
	The company clarified that in 2005-06 and 2006-07 its petroleum products division had made arrangements for import on behalf of licence/permission holders. These holders were responsible for fulfilling all the formalities and paying the duties. Rajesh Adani was not responsible for any day-to-day business operations, the statement added.        
	Till date, no show-cause notices have been registered by the customs department against the group or Rajesh Adani in respect of these transactions, it said.                                                                                                                                       
